<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910408-0011</DOCNO><DOCID>910408-0011.</DOCID><HL>   Harris Corp. Army Contract</HL><DATE>04/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   HRS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>FLORIDA (FL)</RE><LP>   MELBOURNE, Fla. -- Harris Corp. said it was awarded acontract, whose value could approach $1 billion over 15years, to help develop the U.S. Army's new light helicopter.   The maker of office equipment and electronic parts andsystems said its government aerospace systems division willsupply five avionic subsystems for each of the lighthelicopters.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>